oracle.spatial.hadoop.rasterapi.core.jobs

Class RasterLoaderJob

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.spatial.hadoop.rasterapi.core.jobs.RasterJob
      • oracle.spatial.hadoop.rasterapi.core.jobs.RasterLoaderJob

  • public class RasterLoaderJob
extends RasterJob
    Represents a Hadoop job that executes the loading of rasters into HDFS using the received configuration.

      • setFilesToLoad

        public void setFilesToLoad(java.lang.String filesToLoad)

      • addFileToLoad

        public void addFileToLoad(java.lang.String fileToLoad)
        Adds a file to the list of rasters to load by this job
        Parameters:

      • setTileOverlap

        public void setTileOverlap(java.lang.String tileOverlap)
        Sets the overlapping bytes per tile border for this job load
        Parameters:
        tileOverlap - number of overlapping bytes in every raster tile´s border. If none is specified, a default value of 2 is used.

      • dontExpandOutputDir

        public void dontExpandOutputDir()
        Output results will be put in directory without expanding source path

      • setOutputFolder

        public void setOutputFolder(java.lang.String outputFolder)
        Sets the hdfs output folder for the loaded rasters of this job. This value is a must have for job to execute correctly
        Parameters:
        outputFolder - hdfs output folder where .ohif files will be created

      • setRasterThumbnailFolder

        public void setRasterThumbnailFolder(java.lang.String thumbnailFolder)
        Sets the folder to store thumbnails of the rasters loaded by this job. This is an optional setting for loader job
        Parameters:
        thumbnailFolder - the NFS output folder where thumbnails of the loaded rasters can be stored, this folder must be shared across NFS through all nodes and must have write access for every user involved in job execution.

      • execute

        public boolean execute()
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Executes the configured raster loader job. It also validates that all required input configuration has been set correctly.
        Returns:
        true if the job is executed successfully or false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - whenever there is a problem during raster load job execution

      • setGdalPath

        public void setGdalPath(java.lang.String gdalLibPath)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Sets GDAL library path to this job
        Parameters:
        gdalLibPath - path to gdal native libraries path
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - whenever there is a problem during GDAL libraries load into job classpath.
